# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in. NEVER commit real values.
#
# Ingredient enrichment (#11, #59) — an LLM reads raw ingredient lines ("1 (14 oz)
# can", "2-3 cloves", "to taste") into structured data. This runs OFF this service:
# an out-of-band worker (`recipe-backend enrich pull|push`, driven by the enrich
# skill, the recipes-enrich plugin) does the reading and pushes results back. The app
# itself holds no model code, no prompt, and no provider key — none of these belong
# in the deployed service.
#
# The worker hits the app's two machine-gated enrich endpoints — it never touches
# the database (the app is the only writer). So wherever the worker runs it needs:
#   RECIPES_API_URL — the app's base URL (e.g. https://api.recipes.lehlehleh.com)
#   INGEST_API_KEY  — the same machine key that gates /api/ingest (set below/on Render)
#   ENRICH_MODEL    — recorded as each reading's provenance (e.g. claude-opus-4-8)
RECIPES_API_URL=
ENRICH_MODEL=

# Cloudflare R2 — hosts PR screenshots (see #21). Screenshots are rendered from
# Storybook with `nix run .#storybook-shot`, uploaded here, and embedded in the
# PR comment. R2 is free at this size (10 GB storage, egress always free).

# R2 -> Manage R2 API Tokens -> Create API token.
# Scope it: permission "Object Read & Write", limited to the ONE bucket.
# Do NOT use a global Cloudflare API key — that grants the whole account.
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=

# From the S3 client endpoint: https://<account-id>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com
R2_ACCOUNT_ID=
R2_ENDPOINT=
R2_BUCKET=

# The PUBLIC base URL — a different host to the S3 endpoint above, and the one
# GitHub actually needs: Camo fetches images server-side, so the URL must be
# unsigned and non-expiring. Only exists once the bucket has
# Settings -> Public access -> Allow enabled.
#   https://pub-<hash>.r2.dev
R2_PUBLIC_BASE=

# Upload with rclone (NOT awscli — its TLS fails against R2 here, and system
# curl 7.81's --aws-sigv4 omits R2's required x-amz-content-sha256):
#   export RCLONE_CONFIG_R2_TYPE=s3 RCLONE_CONFIG_R2_PROVIDER=Cloudflare
#   export RCLONE_CONFIG_R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=$R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID
#   export RCLONE_CONFIG_R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=$R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
#   export RCLONE_CONFIG_R2_ENDPOINT=$R2_ENDPOINT RCLONE_CONFIG_R2_REGION=auto
#   rclone copy screenshots/ "R2:$R2_BUCKET/recipes/pr-<n>/"
